         - Centralized tracking of all circuit breaker states
         - OpenTelemetry metrics integration (circuit_breaker.state_transitions, circuit_breaker.open_count)
         - Thread-safe concurrent dictionary for state management
         - Well-known service names: AzureOpenAI, AzureAISearch, MicrosoftGraph

      2. Azure AI Search Resilience (ResilientSearchClient.cs):
         - Added circuit breaker, retry, and timeout using Polly v8.x
         - Configurable via AiSearchResilienceOptions (50% failure ratio, 10 min throughput, 30s break)
         - Integrated with CircuitBreakerRegistry for state tracking
         - AiSearchCircuitBrokenException for handling open circuits

      3. Updated OpenAiClient.cs:
         - Integrated with CircuitBreakerRegistry
         - State changes (Open/HalfOpen/Closed) recorded to registry
         - Existing circuit breaker now reports to centralized monitoring

      4. Updated GraphHttpMessageHandler.cs:
         - Integrated with CircuitBreakerRegistry
         - State changes recorded to registry
         - Existing Polly circuit breaker now reports to centralized monitoring

      5. Monitoring Endpoints (ResilienceEndpoints.cs):
         - GET /api/resilience/circuits - All circuit breaker states
         - GET /api/resilience/circuits/{serviceName} - Specific circuit state
         - GET /api/resilience/health - Returns 503 if any circuit is open

      6. Updated RagService.cs:
         - Optional injection of IResilientSearchClient
         - All search, index, and delete operations protected
         - Added AiSearchCircuitBrokenException handling in error paths

